Many other learners have been working in farms, quarries, boda boda trade and hawking in some towns.Central Primary in Eldoret, Uasin Gishu recorded 70 per cent attendance on the first day of term two. Thousands of learners failed to report back to school yesterday, raising fears of mass dropouts across the country.
There have been concerns that many learners will drop out owing to various reasons. Girls are the most affected, with many having become pregnant or married during the time they were out of school.



