Many other learners have been working in farms, quarries, boda boda trade and hawking in some towns.
Some parents have also delayed taking their children back to school having lost their livelihoods through job losses and failed businesses.
In the North Rift region, some learners did not report back due to insecurity, teen pregnancies, early marriages, initiation rites, floods and fears of contracting Covid-19.
Central Primary in Eldoret, Uasin Gishu recorded 70 per cent attendance on the first day of term two.



